31\u067e\u06cc\u0634\u0647\u00bb \u062c\u0644\u0648\u06cc \u062f\u0648\u0631\u0628\u06cc\u0646 \u0645\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u062f]\n*[http://www.aftabir.com/news/view/2012/dec/12/c5_1355308228.php/%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%DA%A9%DB%8C%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%A8%D8%A7-%D9%BE%D9%84%DA%A9%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%B2%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%86-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D8%B5%D8%AD%D9%86%D9%87-%D8%A8%D8%B1%D9%85%DB%8C-%DA%AF%D8%B1%D8%AF%D8%AF \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc \u0628\u0627 \u00ab\u067e\u0644\u06a9\u0627\u0646\u00bb \u0645\u0631\u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u0635\u062d\u0646\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u0645\u06cc \u06af\u0631\u062f\u062f]\n*[http://www.aftabir.com/news/article/view/2016/01/30/1124557 \u067e\u0627\u06cc\u0627\u0646 \u00ab\u062f\u0648\u0631\u062f\u0633\u062a\u200c\u0647\u0627\u00bb \u0628\u0627 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc]\n*[http://www.aftabir.com/news/view/2006/aug/19/c5c1155996329_art_culture_media.php/%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D9%83%DB%8C%D9%85%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2%DB%8C-%DA%A9%D9%87-%D8%AE%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%87%DB%8C%D9%85-%D9%85%D8%B1%D8%AF \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u0643\u06cc\u0645\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u00ab\u0631\u0648\u0632\u06cc \u06a9\u0647 \u062e\u0648\u0627\u0647\u06cc\u0645 \u0645\u0631\u062f \u00bb]\n*https://theater.ir/fa/artists/301\n*https://fa.wikipedia.org/wiki/\u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644_\u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Hakimi, Danial}}\n[[Category:Iranian male film actors]]\n[[Category:Iranian male stage actors]]\n[[Category:Iranian male television actors]]\n[[Category:Iranian male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Male radio actors]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Iranian actor (born 1963)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2016}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Danial Hakimi\n| image              = Danial Hakimi's Portrait.jpg\n| size               = \n| caption            = Danial Hakimi's Portrait\n| native_name_lang   = \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = April 21, 1963\n| birth_place        = [[Shahrud, Iran]]\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| occupation         = Actor\n| salary             = \n| official           = \n| spouse             = \n| father             = \n| children           = 2\n| religion           = \n| television         = \n| education          = Radio acting school in Iran\n| alma_mater         = \n| module             = \n| filename           = \n| title              = \n| type               = \n| description        = \n}}\n\n'''Danial Hakimi''' ({{lang-fa| \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc}}, {{IPAc-en|\u02c8|h|\u00e6|k|\u026a|m|\u026a}}; April 21, 1963) is an [[Iran]]ian film, stage, TV, and radio actor<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftabir.com/articles/view/art_culture/TV/c5c1216455135_daniyal_hakimi_p1.php/%d8%b2%d9%86%d8%af%da%af%db%8c%d9%86%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%87-%d8%af%d8%a7%d9%86%db%8c%d8%a7%d9%84-%d8%ad%da%a9%db%8c%d9%85%db%8c|title=\u0632\u0646\u062f\u06af\u06cc\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc|website=www.aftabir.com|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nHakimi was born in [[Shahrud, Iran]]. He graduated from Radio acting school in Iran, and studied Acting with [[Hamid Samandarian]]. He started his professional acting career by playing as [[Oceanus]], in [[Prometheus Bound]] [[tragedy]] and performed in many notable roles on stage. He went on to [[film]] work, beginning with ''[[:fa:\u0645\u0631\u06af \u062a\u062f\u0631\u06cc\u062c\u06cc \u06cc\u06a9 \u0631\u0624\u06cc\u0627|2001 Inventor]], followed by [[:fa:\u062f\u06cc\u06af\u0647 \u0686\u0647 \u062e\u0628\u0631!\u061f|What's Up?]] and [[:fa:\u0686\u0634\u0645\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc\u0645 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u062a\u0648 (\u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645 \u06f1\u06f3\u06f7\u06f1)|My Eyes for You.]]'' Hakimi, had successful performances in many [[Television show|Television series]] including ''[[:fa:\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0628 \u0648 \u0628\u06cc\u062f\u0627\u0631|Asleep & Awake]]'', ''[[:fa:\u0648\u0644\u0627\u06cc\u062a \u0639\u0634\u0642|Love province]]'', ''[[:fa:\u062e\u0627\u0646\u0647 \u067e\u062f\u0631\u06cc (\u0645\u062c\u0645\u0648\u0639\u0647 \u062a\u0644\u0648\u06cc\u0632\u06cc\u0648\u0646\u06cc)|Paternal House]]'', ''[[:fa:\u0645\u0633\u0627\u0641\u0631 (\u0645\u062c\u0645\u0648\u0639\u0647 \u062a\u0644\u0648\u06cc\u0632\u06cc\u0648\u0646\u06cc)|Passenger]]'', ''[[:fa:\u0641\u06a9\u0631 \u067e\u0644\u06cc\u062f|Evil Mind]]'', and ''[[:fa:\u0645\u0631\u06af \u062a\u062f\u0631\u06cc\u062c\u06cc \u06cc\u06a9 \u0631\u0624\u06cc\u0627|The Gradual Death of a Dream]]''.\n\nIn 2007 he won the '''24th''' [[Fajr International Theater Festival]] award for best performance in the leading role, for the role of Bahman Ahang in the Melody of the Rainy City drama, written by [[:fa:\u0627\u06a9\u0628\u0631 \u0631\u0627\u062f\u06cc|Akbar Radi.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftabir.com/articles/view/art_culture/TV/c5c1216455135_daniyal_hakimi_p1.php/%d8%b2%d9%86%d8%af%da%af%db%8c%d9%86%d8%a7%d9%85%d9%87-%d8%af%d8%a7%d9%86%db%8c%d8%a7%d9%84-%d8%ad%da%a9%db%8c%d9%85%db%8c|title=\u0632\u0646\u062f\u06af\u06cc\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc|website=www.aftabir.com|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n \n[[File:On the scene - Melody Of The Rainy City.jpg|thumb|On the scene \u2013 \"Melody of the Rainy City\" (Drama) Danial Hakimi performing role of \"Bahman Ahang\" City Hall of Tehran, Iran \u2013 Year 2006]]\n\n==Awards and recognition==\n* Appreciation from ''[[:fa:\u0633\u0627\u0632\u0645\u0627\u0646 \u0635\u062f\u0627 \u0648 \u0633\u06cc\u0645\u0627\u06cc \u062c\u0645\u0647\u0648\u0631\u06cc \u0627\u0633\u0644\u0627\u0645\u06cc \u0627\u06cc\u0631\u0627\u0646|IRIB organization]]'' for playing in ''[[:fa:\u0648\u0644\u0627\u06cc\u062a \u0639\u0634\u0642|Love province]]'' TV series 2001\n* Honorary diploma from ''Police festival'' for playing in ''[[:fa:\u062e\u0648\u0627\u0628 \u0648 \u0628\u06cc\u062f\u0627\u0631|Asleep & Awake]]'' TV series 2005\n* Best acting performance in the leading role from ''[[Fajr International Theater Festival|International Fajr theater festival]]'' for playing in ''Melody of the Rainy City'' drama 2005\n* Honorary diploma in title of \"One of the Best Theater Actors\" from ''[http://www.theaterforum.ir House of Theater]'' 2005\n* Appreciation from ''[[:fa:\u0634\u0628\u06a9\u0647 \u062a\u0647\u0631\u0627\u0646|Tehran Channel]]'' in title of \"one of the best actors of Tehran Channel\" for playing in ''[[:fa:\u0631\u0648\u0632 \u0631\u0641\u062a\u0646|The Day We Leave]]'' TV series 2006\n* Honorary diploma from ''[[Jaam-e-Jam (TV channel)|International Jaam-e-Jam channel]]'' in title of \"Best Actor of Jaam-e-Jam Channel\" 2008\n* Trophy and honorary diploma from ''13th anniversary of [http://www.theaterforum.ir/Forums/Criticism-and-Writers-Association National Association of Theater Critics]'' for playing in role of \"Bolbol\" in ''Staircase'' drama 2013<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aftabir.com/news/view/2012/dec/12/c5_1355308228.php/%d8%af%d8%a7%d9%86%db%8c%d8%a7%d9%84-%d8%ad%da%a9%db%8c%d9%85%db%8c-%d8%a8%d8%a7-%d9%be%d9%84%da%a9%d8%a7%d9%86-%d9%85%d8%b1%d8%b2%d8%a8%d8%a7%d9%86-%d8%a8%d9%87-%d8%b5%d8%ad%d9%86%d9%87-%d8%a8%d8%b1%d9%85%db%8c-%da%af%d8%b1%d8%af%d8%af|title=\u062f\u0627\u0646\u06cc\u0627\u0644 \u062d\u06a9\u06cc\u0645\u06cc \u0628\u0627 \"\u067e\u0644\u06a9\u0627\u0646\" \u0645\u0631\u0632\u0628\u0627\u0646 \u0628\u0647 \u0635\u062d\u0646\u0647 \u0628\u0631\u0645\u06cc \u06af\u0631\u062f\u062f|website=www.aftabir.com|access-date=2020-04-15}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Critics Award.jpg|thumb|Trophy and honorary diploma from 13th anniversary of [http://www.theaterforum.ir/Forums/Criticism-and-Writers-Association National Association of Theater Critics] for playing in role of \"Bolbol\" in \"Staircase\" drama (2013)]]\n\n[[File:Danial Hakimi - Warm Soil TV Series.jpg|thumb|Warm Soil TV Series - As \"Professor Brumand\".]]\n\n[[File:Soul Thief.jpg|thumb|Soul Thief TV Series - As \"Nader\"]]\n\n==Filmography==\n* Played in ''[[:fa:\u0634\u06a9\u0627\u0631 \u0631\u0648\u0628\u0627\u0647|Fox Hunting (2008)]]'' Directed by \"[[:fa:\u0645\u062c\u06cc\u062f \u062c\u0648\u0627\u0646\u0645\u0631\u062f|Majid Djavanmard]]\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0627\u0631\u062a\u0641\u0627\u0639 \u06f6/\u06f4\u06f5|Height of 6.75 (2006)]]'' Directed by \"[[:fa:\u0633\u06cc\u0627\u0645\u06a9 \u0634\u0627\u06cc\u0642\u06cc|Siamak Shayeqi]]\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0633\u062a\u0627\u0631\u0647\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u0633\u0631\u0628\u06cc (\u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645)|Lead stars (2002)]]'' Directed by \"[[:fa:\u0645\u0647\u062f\u06cc \u0648\u062f\u0627\u062f\u06cc|Mahdi Vedadi]]\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0637\u0648\u0641\u0627\u0646 (\u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645)|Hurricane (1996)]]'' Directed by \"[[:fa:\u0645\u062d\u0645\u062f \u0628\u0632\u0631\u06af\u200c\u0646\u06cc\u0627|Muhammad Bozorgnia]]\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0644\u0698\u06cc\u0648\u0646 (\u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645 \u06f1\u06f3\u06f7\u06f7)|Legion (1994)]]'' Directed by \"[[:fa:\u0633\u06cc\u062f \u0636\u06cc\u0627\u0621\u0627\u0644\u062f\u06cc\u0646 \u062f\u0631\u06cc|Zia Aldin Dorri]]\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0628\u0627\u0632\u06cc\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc \u067e\u0646\u0647\u0627\u0646|Hidden Games (1994)]]'' Directed by \"Karim Hatefinia\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa:\u0686\u0634\u0645\u200c\u0647\u0627\u06cc\u0645 \u0628\u0631\u0627\u06cc \u062a\u0648 (\u0641\u06cc\u0644\u0645 \u06f1\u06f3\u06f7\u06f1)|My Eyes for You (1992)]]'' Directed by \"Khosrow shojaei\"\n*Played in ''[[:fa